What is Service Control Policy (SCP)?

Service Control Policy (SCP)

A policy that defines the maximum permissions any account/user/role inside that OU can have — even if their IAM policy allows it.

SCP never grants permissions — it only restricts what IAM can do.

SCP is a boundary, not a grant:

Simple Analogy

Normal IAM Policy:
Controls what ONE user/role can do
in ONE account

SCP:
Controls what EVERYONE can do
across ALL accounts
Even the account's root user cannot bypass it
→ like a company-wide rule
   that even managers must follow

-------------
How SCP Works

Management Account
        │
        ▼
   Applies SCP
        │
        ▼
┌───────────────────────────────┐
│  OU Production                │
│    ├── Prod Account           │
│    │     └── All users/roles  │  ← SCP applies to everyone
│    └── DR Account             │
│          └── All users/roles  │  ← SCP applies here too
└───────────────────────────────┘

Even if IAM policy ALLOWS something,
SCP can still DENY it ✅

-------

SCP vs IAM Policy

IAM Policy  +  SCP  =  Final Permission
─────────────────────────────────────────
ALLOW       +  ALLOW =  ✅ Allowed
ALLOW       +  DENY  =  ❌ Denied   ← SCP wins
DENY        +  ALLOW =  ❌ Denied   ← IAM wins
DENY        +  DENY  =  ❌ Denied

Example 3 — Block Public S3

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{
    "Effect": "Deny",
    "Action": "s3:PutBucketPublicAccessBlock",
    "Resource": "*"
  }]
}
→ Nobody can make S3 bucket public

Example 4 — Prevent Deleting CloudTrail

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{
    "Effect": "Deny",
    "Action": [
      "cloudtrail:DeleteTrail",
      "cloudtrail:StopLogging"
    ],
    "Resource": "*"
  }]
}
→ Nobody can disable audit logging

Where SCP is Applied

Root → applies to ALL accounts
  │
  OU → applies to accounts in that OU
    │
    Account → applies to that account only

---
Key Points

✅ SCP does NOT grant permissions
✅ SCP only RESTRICTS permissions
✅ Even root user cannot bypass SCP
✅ Management account is NOT affected by SCP
✅ Must have Organizations enabled

------------------
How to Access SCP

AWS Console (Easiest)

1. Login → Management Account
2. Search "AWS Organizations"
3. Left menu → "Policies"
4. Click → "Service Control Policies"
5. Click "Enable SCPs" (first time)
6. Create / Attach / Detach SCPs
